text: Aksaitovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Aksaitovsky Selsoviet, Tatyshlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 794 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 21 km from Verkhniye Tatyshly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tatyshlinsky District
title: Aksaitovo
